 in Asia but in other parts of the world, has prompted warnings of an imminent "clash of civilizations" between Islam and the West. Islam in an Era of Nation-States examines the history, politics, and meanings of this resurgence in Indonesia, Malaysia, and the Philippines and explores its implications for Southeast Asia, the larger Muslim world, and the West. This volume will be of interest to students of Islam, Southeast Asian history, and the anthropology of religion. In examining the politics and meanings of Islamic resurgence, it will also speak to political scientists, religious scholars, and others concerned with culture and politics in the late modern era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aIslam and politicszSoutheast Asia. 0aIslam and statezSoutheast Asia. 0aIslam and world politics. 0aIslamy20th century. 0aIslamic fundamentalismzSoutheast Asia. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh1 aBowen, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeillard, Andrée, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHefner, Robert W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHefner, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorvatich, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorvatich, Patricia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMcKenna, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMetcalf, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeletz, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRössler, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShamsul, A.B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relat